705523f-a.title: Brooklyn: Lynch Street - Harrison Avenue
705523f-a.text:
(1)
Lynch Street, west from Harrison Ave. At right foreground, is a
view of the 47th Regiment headquarters of the N.Y. State Armory.
October 1928.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(2)
Same, showing view on Marcy Ave. Corner stone laid in 1883.
October 1928.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REEODUCED.

705524f-a.title: Brooklyn: Lynch Street - Harrison Avenue
705524f-a.text:
Lynch Street, south side, between Harrison Street and Broadway. In the
foreground, buildings have been razed to make way for the Eighth Ave., Muni.
cipal Subway. The rear vdew of the frame houses, are on Midcleton Street.
